From: Nikami Worlds <nikami-worlds@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 23:05:00 -0700
Subject: [experiment] ESM4 actor controller basis audit

Status: experiment, not queued in patches/openmw/series.
Depends-on: 0010-esm4-face-rig-render-buffer-audit.patch.
Proof baseline: run/proof-harness-sweeps/20260707-223752.

After 0010, FO3/FNV face attachment telemetry passes but the close-burst
screenshots still show inverted/disassembled actors. The next suspect is the
Fallout actor controller basis: the active source samples keyframes with an
extra half-turn/bind basis baked into NifOsg::KeyframeController, while the
HIGGS-lite branch exposes raw sampling and only applies that basis explicitly.

This patch preserves current behavior. It adds a raw controller-sampling helper
and logs per-bone deltas when OPENMW_FNV_ACTOR_BASIS_AUDIT=1 is set, so the next
proof can compare basis-applied and raw controller rotations before trying
another behavior change.

